decision_conditions:
FORMAL DECISION

The Planning Inspectorate allow the appeal and grant planning permission for amendment in course of construction to dormer window in east elevation, new doors, railings and planting strip at 317-318 Upper Street, Islington, London N1 in accordance with the terms of the application reference: P040059 dated 7th January 2004 and the plans submitted therewith, subject to the following conditions:

1)  the development hereby permitted shall begin before the expiration of five years from the date of this decision;

2)  no development shall take place until samples of the materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  Development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details;

3)  the infill between the balustrade and parapet shall be of opaque/frosted glass and shall be permanently so retained;

4)  access onto the planting strip shown on drawing 1218/42 (or any subsequently approved amendment) shall be for maintenance purposes only.
